cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with policy gradient methods in reinforcement learning. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as RL is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.RO (Robotics) as RL is often used in robotics applications. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as RL is used in control systems. Finally, it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as policy gradient methods are often used in neural network training.
